What you ARE allowed to do
--------------------------

You are free to:

• View and study the source code
• Compile and run the software for yourself
• Modify the code for personal, educational, or internal use
• Learn from the architecture, ideas, and implementation

---

What you are NOT allowed to do
------------------------------

You may NOT, without explicit written permission from the author:

• Sell the software, in whole or in part
• Distribute paid binaries or installers
• Offer the software as part of a paid product or service
• Rebrand, fork, or adapt the software and sell it as a competing product
• Use the software to provide paid consulting, support, or hosted services

In short: you may not make money from Lingr or its derivatives.

